<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1523,1800]" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1905" box="[151,269,1523,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Phassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,269,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Phassodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only exoporian genus endemic to small volcanic islands in the Southwest Pacific (
<figureCitation box="[1266,1350,1523,1548]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1782,1805]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,337,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[152,1435,337,1761]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Fig. 9. Distribution of oxycanine groups: Neohepialiscus (North Africa), Hepialiscus (Himalaya-southern Asia), Napialus (China), Oxycanus (New Guinea-Australia), and New Zealand oxycanine genera. Fig. 10. Known and potential distribution of Phassodes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066398/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). There appear to be different species on each of the islands of 
<collectingCountry box="[797,996,1559,1584]" name="American Samoa" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">American Samoa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1052,1559,1584]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1141,1560,1584]" name="Samoa" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Samoa</collectingCountry>
and the 
<collectingCountry box="[1246,1436,1559,1584]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(Grehan &amp; Mielke in prep.). Biogeographic connections involving these and other nearby islands are common. Examples include the plant genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1834" box="[546,615,1632,1655]" class="Aves" family="Cettiidae" genus="Cettia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,615,1632,1655]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Cettia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[654,726,1632,1656]" name="Tonga" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Tonga</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[740,782,1631,1656]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, Solomons, Bougainville, 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1149,1631,1656]" name="Palau" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Palau</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1163,1289,1631,1656]" name="Philippines" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Philippines</collectingCountry>
and Europe, but missing 
<collectingCountry box="[292,388,1669,1692]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
; the warbler genus 
<taxonomicName box="[612,755,1668,1693]" class="Aves" family="Locustellidae" genus="Megalurulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[612,755,1668,1693]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Megalurulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[795,837,1668,1693]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[850,945,1669,1692]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[958,1136,1668,1693]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, Solomons (Guadalcanal), Bougainville, and New Britain; a clade of stick insects in the 
<collectingCountry box="[861,1012,1703,1728]" name="Cook Islands" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Cook Islands</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1068,1703,1728]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1081,1273,1703,1728]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
, New 
<collectingCountry box="[1348,1432,1703,1728]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and Lord Howe Island/ 
<collectingCountry box="[410,515,1740,1765]" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Australia</collectingCountry>
; the frog genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1858" box="[692,825,1740,1765]" class="Amphibia" family="Ceratobatrachidae" genus="Platymantis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anura" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[692,825,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Platymantis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[860,902,1740,1765]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, Solomons Islands, New 
<collectingCountry box="[1184,1268,1740,1765]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1344,1740,1765]" name="Palau" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Palau</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,281,1775,1800]" name="Philippines" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Philippines</collectingCountry>
; the stick insect 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1907" box="[469,630,1775,1800]" class="Insecta" family="Phasmatidae" genus="Phasmotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phasmida" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[469,630,1775,1800]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Phasmotaenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[668,710,1775,1800]" name="Fiji" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, Solomons, New 
<collectingCountry box="[910,994,1775,1800]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1006,1135,1775,1800]" name="Philippines" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1326,1775,1800]" name="Micronesia" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
; the palm
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1857,2033]" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">
1. The molecular analysis is problematic because it groups 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meyrick, 1890)" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[777,1176,1857,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Oxycanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphragidias">
<emphasis box="[777,1003,1857,1879]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Oxycanus sphragidias</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick, E." box="[1016,1169,1857,1879]" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" pagination="1117 - 1216" refId="ref20262" refString="Meyrick, E. (1890) Revision of Australian Lepidoptera. III. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 4, 1117 - 1216. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 15082" type="journal article" year="1890">Meyrick, 1890</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" box="[1235,1319,1858,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Trictena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1235,1319,1858,1879]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Trictena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than with other oxycanine species. But the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[793,1022,1888,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Oxycanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphragidias">
<emphasis box="[793,1022,1888,1910]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Oxycanus sphragidias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibit only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1856" box="[1167,1267,1889,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Oxycanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1167,1267,1889,1910]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Oxycanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
features (J.R.G. personal observation) and so lack any specific resemblance to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" box="[829,913,1920,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Trictena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[829,913,1920,1941]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Trictena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(or the related 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grehan" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[1068,1182,1919,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Abantiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1182,1919,1941]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">Abantiades</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Simonsen, T. J." box="[1237,1396,1919,1941]" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" pagination="1 - 312" refId="ref22148" refString="Simonsen, T. J. (2018) Splendid ghost moths and their allies. A revision of Australian Abantiades, Oncopera, Aenetus, Archaeoaenetus and Zelotypia. Monographs on Australian Lepidoptera, 12, 1 - 312." type="journal article" year="2018">Simonsen 2018</bibRefCitation>
, for descriptions of all 
<emphasis box="[386,592,1949,1971]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1890" box="[386,467,1949,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Trictena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trictena</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Grehan" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[479,592,1949,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Abantiades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Abantiades</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
species). This anomaly places the entire molecular tree in doubt. Direct assessment of possible contamination or other causes of error cannot be assessed, as the voucher specimen for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1890" box="[1210,1362,1980,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Oxycanus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="252" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sphragidias">
<emphasis box="[1210,1362,1980,2002]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="252">O. sphragidias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be located and all frozen specimens appear to have been discarded (John Marris, pers. comm.)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">
<taxonomicName box="[151,301,151,176]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Heterospathe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="10" pageNumber="253" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,301,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Heterospathe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[342,384,151,176]" name="Fiji" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[397,590,151,176]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
, New Britain, New 
<collectingCountry box="[824,908,151,176]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[922,1100,151,176]" name="Indonesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Maluku Islands</collectingCountry>
, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1338,151,176]" name="Philippines" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Philippines</collectingCountry>
; and the beetle 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuschel" authorityYear="2008" box="[235,399,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Allorthorhinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[235,399,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Allorthorhinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[457,499,188,213]" name="Fiji" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[520,721,188,213]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[801,927,188,213]" name="Philippines" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Heads, M." box="[953,1115,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="253" refId="ref19284" refString="Heads, M. (2017 a) Biogeography and Evolution in New Zealand. CRC Press, Boca Raton, 635 pp." type="book" year="2017">Heads 2017a</bibRefCitation>
). In the context of these biogeographic relationships it is not unexpected that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bethune-Baker" authorityYear="1905" box="[775,893,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Hepialidae" genus="Phassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="253" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[775,893,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Phassodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be found to occur more widely over the northern Melanesian Arc (
<figureCitation box="[446,527,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–10" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1782,1805]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,337,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[152,1435,337,1761]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 9–10. Fig. 9. Distribution of oxycanine groups: Neohepialiscus (North Africa), Hepialiscus (Himalaya-southern Asia), Napialus (China), Oxycanus (New Guinea-Australia), and New Zealand oxycanine genera. Fig. 10. Known and potential distribution of Phassodes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066398/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) and perhaps further west into northern New 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1119,260,285]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="10" pageNumber="253">Guinea</collectingCountry>
and Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3066398/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="253" startId="10.[151,264,1782,1805]" targetBox="[152,1435,337,1761]" targetPageId="10">
